         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">28/1/88. ¶  ¶ It seems, esteemed Mr Tepper, that letters from us were underway simultaneously. I already wrote to you some days ago ¶  and then sent the letter about the Characeae back, also advised t...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">88.01.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Tepper</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M198, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Tepper: 'Reply with specimen of Red Mallee (small […] bushes) &amp; Schleranthus 3.2.88'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>28/1/88.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es scheint, geehrter Herr Tepper, dass Breife von uns gleichzeitig unterwegs waren. Ich schrieb Ihnen schon vor einigen Tagen, u sandte dann den Brief über die Characeen zurück, rieth auch, Ihre Abhandlung über Xanthorroea der R.S. von Tasmania zugänglich zu machen, zumal da auch eine Art da vorkommt.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Der scheinbare Exogenismus der <name key="Xanthorrhoea">Xanthorrhoea</name> lässt auf Verhältnisse zurückführen, die auch bei einigen andere palmstämmigen Liliaceen vorkommen; und es würde dann nöthig sein, </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">diese</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> im Zusammenhang zu erörtern, ehe eine Schrift darüber der </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Linné-Gesellschaft</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">, welche so viele Critiker hat, vorgelegt wird. Ich bin noch weit mit dem "Key" zurück durch tägliche dringende Unterbrechungen, so weit, dass ich für Monate keiner solchen Arbeit als der vergleichenden Anatomie der Liliaceen-Stämme irgend Zeit widmen könnte.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Da ich mich also eingehend </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">jetzt</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> nicht dabei betheiligen könnte, wäre es besser, einer </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">anspruchslosener</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Gesellschaft, am Besten einer in Australien, Ihre Schrift vorzulegen. In Tasmanien wäre auch gute Gelegenheit, die Platten zu liefern.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In der nächsten Woche will ich einige freie Stunden zu erhaschen suchen, um wenigstens die Namen der </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">genera</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> zu Ihren W.A. Pflanzen zu schreiben; leider haben die Pflanzen wenig Werth da wir die genauen Standorte nicht kennen.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Mit freundsch. Grusse</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Der spätere Gebrauch des Key wird nie für jetztigen Mangel an Hülfe ganz entschädigen.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28/1/88.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It seems, esteemed Mr Tepper, that letters from us were underway simultaneously. I already wrote to you some days ago<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to O. Tepper, 23 January 1888.</p>
               </note> and then sent the letter about the <name key="Characeae">Characeae</name> back, also advised that you make your paper on <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Xanthorrhoea">Xanthorrhoea</name>
               </seg> available to the Royal Society of Tasmania,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter of advice not found. No paper on <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Xanthorrhoea">Xanthorrhoea</name>
                     </seg> by Tepper was published by the Royal Society of Tasmania.</p>
               </note> especially since a species also occurs there.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The apparent exogenism of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Xanthorrhoea">Xanthorrhoea</name>
               </seg> can be traced back to the conditions that also occur in some other palm-trunked <name key="Liliaceae">Liliaceae</name>, and it would then be necessary to discuss <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">the latter</hi>
               </seg> in context before a paper on it is submitted to the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Linnean Society</hi>
               </seg>, which has so many critics. I am still far behind with the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Key</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B88.11.02.</p>
               </note> through daily pressing interruptions, so far that for months I could not devote any time to any such work as the comparative anatomy of the <name key="Liliaceae">Liliaceae</name> stems.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since I therefore could not participate in it fully <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">now</hi>
               </seg>, it would be better to submit your paper to an <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">undemanding</hi>
               </seg> society, the best one in Australia. In Tasmania there would also be a good opportunity to provide the plates.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Next week I shall try to catch some free hours to at least ascribe the names of the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">genera</hi>
               </seg> to your Western Australian plants; unfortunately the plants have little value since we don't know the exact localities.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">With friendly greetings</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The later use of the Key will never quite compensate for the present lack of assistance.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Characeae">Characeae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Liliaceae">Liliaceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Xanthorrhoea">Xanthorrhoea</name>
            </p>
         </div>
